JM, mind fixing the likes of the below. In hbase codebase, the 'false' gets curly braces around it.


 12 +    if (obj == null || getClass() != obj.getClass())

 13 +      return false;

Also, you seem to add some imports though they are not used 'Delayed' and 'Row'.

Is this right in NullComparator?


16 +  public boolean equals(Object obj) {

 17 +    return obj == null;

 18 +  }

Thanks for doing these findbug issues. I'll update our tolerated findbugs count after this goes in. It is falling fast.

Update version with additionnal brackets attached.

Regarding the NullComparator, here is the compareTo code:


  @Override

  public int compareTo(byte[] value) {

    return value != null ? 1 : 0;

  }

It's return equels only if the given byte array is null. So I have replicated the same behaviour on the equalsTo methode.

I have more modifications coming to fix other findbug issues. I will try to get them down one by one...
